<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-545-557  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 545 557.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Reseller News  Feb 26 1990 n356 p47(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Novell NLM program: reacting to charges. (certification programfor NetWare Loadable Modules)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Shore, Joel.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Novell Inc introduces a certification program, scheduled to beginin the 2nd qtr of 1990, for NetWare Loadable Modules (NLM),apparently reacting to insinuation from the LAN Manager camp thatfaulty NLMs may cause server memory management problems.andP;  Theprogram, which has an initial entry charge of $10,000, has causedvarious reactions ranging from enthusiastic endorsements to dismayat the high fees.andP;  An NLM that does not pass testing can beretested within 90 days for $6,000.andP;  Tests of an updated versionof a previously certified NLM or retesting of a previouslycertified version with a new release of NetWare 386 costs $8,000.andO;Novell officials state the firm is not out to make money on thesetests.andP;  Five key developers have already enrolled in the program,including Oracle, Informix Software, XDB Systems and Retix.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Novell Inc. (product development).andO;Ticker:    NOVL.andO;Topic:     CertificationTestingAdd-In-On SoftwareLocal Area NetworksNetwork Management SoftwareNetwork Operating Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>